		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By Suzanne Lainson, 8-07-05</b>
		<p>I'm glad to see the album reviewed. I think it's an exceptional album and hope more people have a chance to listen to it. I'm 56 and some of the songs very much remind me of music I heard in the 1950s and 1960s. <br />
<br />
Some of them have a 60s slow dance beat to them. Recently I heard Leslie Gore's "You Don't Own Me" and the Righteous Brothers "Unchained Melody" on the radio and thought, "Yes!" that's what I hear on Angie's album. <br />
<br />
Other songs remind me of stuff that the Grand Ole Opry was playing on its radio broadcasts years ago.<br />
<br />
And the vulnerability in her voice is reminiscent of bluegrass singers.<br />
<br />
She's also worth seeing live. There's an intensity to her performances which I can only compare to Janis Joplin or Judy Garland. Not the same kind of music, but the same total involvement.</p>
		
